<div class="badge"><span class="badge-dot"></span>Buyer's question</div>
<h1 class="hero-h">AI Audit vs AI Strategy Engagement <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">One produces a roadmap; the other produces a deck.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">Two common first engagement types in the AI consulting world. They sound similar; they produce very different outputs. If you are choosing between them, here's what each actually delivers and which is right for you.</p>
<div class="tldr"><div class="tldr-l">Short answer</div><p class="tldr-p">An AI audit produces a written, prioritized roadmap with specific workflows, owners, and timelines (\$1.5K-\$15K, 1-3 weeks). An AI strategy engagement produces a longer narrative deck about vision, positioning, and direction (\$15K-\$80K, 6-12 weeks). Most mid-market companies need the audit, not the strategy.</p></div>
</div></div>

<div style="background:#0A1A0A;border-top:1px solid #1A3A1A;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.25rem 2.5rem;">
<div style="max-width:880px;margin:0 auto;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;font-size:0.78rem;color:#8FAF8F;">
<div>By <a href="/about" style="color:#F0FFF0;text-decoration:none;font-weight:500;">Bill Colbert</a> · <span style="color:#4A6A4A;">Founder, Treetop Growth Strategy</span></div>
<div style="color:#4A6A4A;">Published May 2026 · <a href="/content-library" style="color:#8FAF8F;text-decoration:none;">More from the library</a></div>
</div>
</div>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">What an AI audit produces</h2><ul class="ul"><li>Written report: where AI fits your business, ranked by leverage.</li><li>Specific workflow recommendations with owners and effort estimates.</li><li>Tool platform recommendation (Claude / ChatGPT / Copilot / hybrid).</li><li>90-day action plan with milestones.</li><li>Optional: budget estimate and implementation partner recommendations.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">What an AI strategy engagement produces</h2><ul class="ul"><li>Vision statement and strategic narrative.</li><li>Market positioning around AI.</li><li>Long-form analysis of competitive AI landscape.</li><li>Multi-year transformation roadmap (often vague on execution).</li><li>Executive deck for board / investor presentation.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Which to pick</h2><p class="body">If you are a $5M-$50M B2B company that has not deployed AI yet: <strong>start with the audit</strong>. The strategy adds delay; the audit causes action.</p><p class="body">If you are an enterprise considering multi-year AI investments across business units: an AI strategy may be warranted, particularly if board narrative matters.</p><p class="body">If you are about to raise capital and investors want to see an AI thesis: a strategy engagement may pay for itself in pitch credibility.</p></div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">FAQ</h2>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Can one engagement produce both?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Sometimes. Most good firms include strategic framing in their audit deliverable. Pure strategy engagements often skip the actionable roadmap, which is the part you actually need.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">How long does each take?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Audit: 1-3 weeks. Strategy: 6-12 weeks.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">How much does each cost?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Audit: \$1.5K-\$15K. Strategy: \$15K-\$80K.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Will I need both?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Most $5M-$50M companies need only the audit. Enterprises sometimes need both.</p></div>
</div></section>

